1 (5) Each electric provider shall meet the renewable energy
2 credit standard, subject to subsection (3), with renewable energy
3 credits obtained by any of the following means:
4 (a) Generating electricity from renewable energy systems for
5 sale to retail customers.
6 (b) Purchasing or otherwise acquiring renewable energy and
7 capacity.
8 (c) Purchasing or otherwise acquiring renewable energy credits
9 without the associated renewable energy or capacity. Renewable
10 energy credits acquired under this subdivision shall be produced
11 within the territory of the regional transmission organization of
12 which the electric provider is a member, and, except for a
13 municipally owned electric utility, shall not exceed 5% of an
14 electric provider's renewable energy credits annually used to
15 comply with the renewable energy standard. Renewable energy credits
16 acquired under this subdivision are not subject to the requirements
17 of section 29 and shall not be used to comply with the renewable
18 energy standard after 2035.
19 (6) For an electric provider whose rates are regulated by the
20 commission, the electric provider shall submit a contract entered
21 into for the purposes of subsection (5) to the commission for
22 review and approval. If the commission approves the contract, it is
23 considered consistent with the electric provider's renewable energy
24 plan. The commission shall not approve a contract based on an
25 unsolicited proposal unless the commission determines that the
26 unsolicited proposal provides opportunities that may not otherwise
27 be available or commercially practical through a competitive bid
28 process.
29 (7) An electric provider that has achieved annual incremental
TMV H02140'25 (H-1) gx2hk3

5
1 energy savings of greater than 2% under an energy waste reduction
2 plan approved under section 73 may substitute energy waste
3 reduction credits for renewable energy credits otherwise required
4 to meet the renewable energy credit standard if the substitution is
5 approved by the commission. Under this subsection, energy waste
6 reduction credits shall not be used by a provider to meet more than
7 10% of the renewable energy credit standard. One renewable energy
8 credit shall be awarded per 1 energy waste reduction credit.
9 (8) If an electric provider whose rates are regulated by the
10 commission enters into a purchase power agreement for renewable
11 energy resources or a third-party contract for an energy storage
12 system or clean energy system with an entity that is not an
13 affiliate, the commission shall authorize an annual financial
14 incentive for the electric provider. The financial incentive shall
15 be calculated as the product of contract payments in that year
16 multiplied by the electric provider's pre-tax weighted average cost
17 of permanent capital comprised of long-term debt obligations and
18 equity of the electric provider's total capital structure as
19 determined by the commission's final order in the electric
20 provider's most recent general rate case. The pre-tax weighted
21 average cost of permanent capital used to calculate the financial
22 incentive shall not be fixed throughout the entire term of the
23 contract at the pre-tax weighted average cost of capital applicable
24 in the first year but shall be updated based on the commission's
25 final order in each succeeding general rate case for the electric
26 provider. The financial incentive shall apply to each contract
27 described in this subsection from the date the contract is executed
28 for the entire term of the contract. This subsection applies to any
29 contract entered into after June 30, 2024.
